volume.name: A Little Book of Magical Beings

description: Preview guide to upcoming Season One titles in 2012. Includes material from the Season One graphic novels of Ant-Man, Hulk, and Doctor Strange.
name: Ant-Man Season One/Hulk Season One/Doctor Strange Season One

description: Collects WONDER WOMAN #212-222. In these 1970s tales, Diana Prince is back as Wonder Woman – but she must prove her worthiness by undertaking twelve tasks – each monitored by one of her former Justice League teammates!
name: TPB

description: After the fall of New Genesis, the Justice League regroups with the New Gods on Apokolips--to prepare for all-out war! But do they have the firepower to stop a threat that can literally destroy planets?
name: Prophets of Ophidia

description:
IDW’s newly recolored reprints of classic Doctor Who tales from years past, this time featuring the SIXTH DOCTOR, concludes! The Doctor, Peri, and Frobisher deliver a present to a jazzy birthday bash, only to unleash a self-replicating robot that threatens the planet in “The Gift.”

Originally printed in Doctor Who Magazine #123-126.
name: The Gift

description: Great jumping on point as the next chapter begins here. It's 1961 and Fury gets a new assignment: The Assassination of Fidel Castro!
name: My War Gone By Issue 4: If We Was Meant to Be Cowboys

description: Chaos ensues as both sides join the battle. Weaver and the fighters are holding firm, protecting the evacuation efforts. And when the last are out, they make their final stand in a blaze of glory: they set fire to the city. The Battle of Fitchburg is ended.

volume.name: Falling Skies: The Battle of Fitchburg

description: It's Christmas Eve, and the Beagle Boys are planning a big heist at the Bank of Duckburg! In the meantime, Grandpa Beagle has won the lottery and decides to deposit the money right into the bank chosen by his nephews...

volume.name: The Beagle Boys and the Christmas Surprise

description: John Carter has freed Mars from Issus, the false and now thoroughly dead goddess who once ruled the entire planet. In doing so he lost his one true love, the princess Dejah Thoris, but there's no time to mope--renegade priests of Issus have activated a doomsday device that will destroy Mars's fragile atmosphere, unless Carter can figure out a way to shut it down. He and his son, Carthoris, have no choice but to turn to the people they most despise, the Holy Therns. Carthoris catches the eye of a beautiful princess, but what will his father think?
name: Worms of Mars - Part 1
